  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Placed at junctions where two channels join, used to indicate preferred channel. It can be thought of as a "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "1d098489-7f4f-4caa-9386-3905e3bf4b70"
          },
          {
            "s": "Lateral Mark"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " on the preferred channel. "
        },
        [
          "transclude",
          "@00e28f42-e660-4ff2-961c-a91dbaa6ecc7"
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "In the above diagram, the preferred channel mark is marking the "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "d2a36747-869a-4b48-8419-21fb887c0317"
          },
          {
            "s": "Starboard"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " side of the preferred channel, hence the main characteristics of the mark are the same as a "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "d5908341-d55f-413f-bb10-eda2f4d54400"
          },
          {
            "s": "Starboard Lateral Mark"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". However, to indicate that "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "1a8d73f1-d55e-4086-9112-bb7d82af4abb"
          },
          {
            "s": "Port"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " is the preferred channel, it has a red band in the middle."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "!Preferred Channel Mark.base"
        }
      ]
    ],
